  "exp102_implication": "The M3 pseudo-T hypothesis (low M3 = higher detection) is not supported at cohort level. An M3 < threshold gate for EXP-102 cannot be justified by this data as the mechanism for B > A > C. Alternative hypotheses for wave-1 advantage: (1) curation selection bias in EXP-001 population, (2) instrument sensitivity to project scale/n_authors rather than Galois closure structure, (3) observation window artifacts. EXP-102 design requires new preregistration rationale."
